TrackingWide (200–400 units).
WeightLight to Regular. Never Bold on body.

Garment coloursBone, Washed Black, Stone.
ForbiddenBright, neon, pastels, seasonal.
04
Visual Mood & Editorial
▶
"It's not about the shape of the hole. It's about how the needle is threading, how you care for the cut... It has to be editorial."
— Editorial direction meeting, Feb 2026

Show the details, not the full product. Craftsmanship, texture, care.

ElementDirection
PhotographyTonal, low-to-medium contrast, warm light, quiet/reflective
FocusDetails first: stitching, fabric grain, label, drape, texture
CompositionGenerous negative space. Subject rarely fills frame.
LightingNatural or warm studio. Never harsh flash. Shadow is friend.
MoodSolitary, confident, early morning or golden hour.
EnvironmentRecurring visual world. Concrete + natural elements.
Visual Direction (generated)
Editorial mood — solitary figure, bone garment, warm concrete, golden hour. The tone we're building toward.
Detail — fabric weight, construction
Material — tonal fabric swatches
Wolf in the visual language
Shadows, silhouettes, movement — not just a logo. Never cartoonish, never aggressive. "If you know, you know."
05
SEALCAM Analysis Framework
▶

Every reference image gets decomposed into 6 elements before we write a single prompt.

S
Subject
Who or what is the main focus. Wolf mark, model, garment, detail shot.
E
Environment
Physical setting, background, surfaces. Concrete, natural light, studio.
A
Action
What is happening. Stillness counts. Drape of fabric, gaze, gesture.
L
Lighting
Mood, direction, intensity. Warm studio, golden hour, shadow play.
C
Camera
Device, lens, focal length, angle, movement. Sony A7IV, 85mm, f/1.8.
M
Meta-tokens
Production cues: film grain, colour grade, era, quality tier, aesthetic.

Every existing slide shot and wolf exploration gets a SEALCAM analysis. These text descriptions become the foundation for every generation prompt.

06
What the Brand Is / Is Not
▶

THE BRAND IS

  • Quiet confidence
  • Self-made, self-reliant
  • Controlled, restrained, intelligent
  • Tonal, textured, earned
  • Nigerian-rooted, globally relevant
  • Editorial, detail-focused
  • Premium essentials with narrative depth
  • Conceptual content (wolf as engine)

THE BRAND IS NOT

  • Fast fashion or trend-driven
  • Graphic-heavy or loud
  • Aggressive or wild (wolf is never feral)
  • Hype-focused or drop-culture
  • Minimalist-only lookbook (era ending)
  • Generic product-on-white shots
  • Script fonts, neon, seasonal colours
  • Copying ALD (Aimé Leon Dore) without concept
Quiet confidence — solitary, self-possessed, unhurried. This is the brand.

The tension: Quiet enough for FOG/Yeezy — conceptual enough not to disappear. The wolf is the bridge.

07
Generation Pipeline & Budget
▶

Never prompt from scratch. Always start with references.

1
Reference
Gather visual starting points
▶

Existing: 6 slide shots, 2 wolf explorations, hoodie mockup.

Additional: Competitor lookbooks, typography-in-context, editorial benchmarks.

Describe then prompt

SEALCAM text descriptions become prompts. Never skip the analysis step.

2
Analyse
SEALCAM decomposition
▶

SEALCAM decomposition → structured text output. Analysis and creation are separate steps.

Inspectable stages

Prompts (free) → Images ($0.02-0.05) → Curation. Catch errors at cheapest stage.

3
Prompt
1 direction → N unique prompts
▶

One direction + SEALCAM → N unique prompts, each varying angle/environment/lighting.

Contact sheets: 2x3 grids for consistency. Asymmetric prompting: Primary = detailed, secondary = minimal shift.

All prompts constrained by config.json (palette, type, editorial rules).

4
Generate
kie.ai API → raw/ folder
▶
TaskModelCost
Wolf marksGPT-Image-1~$0.03
WordmarksIdeogram V3~$0.035
MockupsFlux Kontext Pro~$0.025
EditorialNanoBanana Pro~$0.025

Models not locked — assigned based on test results. Max 25 per batch.

5
Curate
Labeled PDF → voice note review
▶

Generate → curate → labeled PDF (A1, A2, A3...) → share → voice note feedback → iterate.

Review images, not prompts. Faster to evaluate visually.
